RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 7000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF A RACE IN 2023 OR NON WINNERS OF FOUR RACES LIFETIME. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 5000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500. Colorado Bred Claiming Price $3,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SILVER PONZI co-led from the inside to the five sixteenths pole then edged away and drew clear. OMACHE KID tracked the leaders from the inside around the turn then cut the corner and slipped through to prove second best. GRAYDAR'S DREAM co-led from the two path to the five sixteenths and gave way grudginly. RHODIUM RUNNER was three wide through the turn and made a late run to pass tiring rivals. EXPECT ROYAL raced at the back through the turn then moved out to mid track to improve position. WILD FIREMAKER was off the pace from two wide around the turn, tipped out to four wide in upper stretch but failed to menace. CHERUBIM raced near the back around the turn then made a mild bid in the stretch but was out finished.

ENTRY.NAME: Omache Kid
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders, slipped through, second best,

ENTRY.NAME: Cherubim
ENTRY.COMMENT: near back, mild bid stretch, out finished

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 6800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF TWO RACES IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Colorado Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CATS GOTTA CHANCE was hustled along to take a pressured lead to the quarter pole then edged away and drew off. HEADEDTOTHESTARS raced off the pace, going three wide around the turn and into the stretch but was no match for the winner. EL CHUMELITO saved ground throughout and was along for the show. TIGER THE MAN raced near the back and passed the tiring rival. CLEARLY MAD pressed the pace from the two path to the quarter pole and gave way. MY TRUE REWARD trailed the field and was outrun.

ENTRY.COMMENT: pressured lead, edged away, drew off,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Special Weight Purse 9700. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRACIE'S A TIGER sprinted away to set all the pace and proved much the best. STARLET COLE raced in the middle of the pack to the turn then moved up from three wide around the turn but was no match for the winner. IMA HOT TOTTIE prompted the pace from the two path to the three furlong marker and flattened out. AUNT CARI had no early speed, saved ground around the turn and moved between horses at the three sixteenths pole to improve her position in the stretch. CANDIED JOULE was always back. GOSPEL GLORY saved ground to no avail.

ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, saved ground turn, between horses, improved

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 8100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR COLORADO BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES LIFETIME. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Colorado Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIXIEMAGIC raced in the middle of the pack down the backstretch then moved up from three wide around the turn and dug in in the stretch, took over in deep stretch and drew clear. BORN TO RACE was last away, steadily advanced up the rail through the turn, rallied by moving out to two wide at the eighth pole and tipping out to three wide at the sixteenth pole but was too late. EUSEBIO rushed up to a clear lead to the eighth pole then was collared in the final sixteenth but was a game third. GO LAKER GO tracked the leaders from off the rail on the backstretch, dropped back around the turn, angled out to four wide in upper stretch but was empty. MUCHO GIFTED was off the pace to the top of the stretch and tired. BUMPER POOL was never involved. CHARLIE'S NO SAINT was outrun.

ENTRY.COMMENT: rushed to lead, collared, game third

ENTRY.NAME: Born to Race
ENTRY.COMMENT: last away, steady advance, 2w1/8, 3w1/16, too late

ENTRY.NAME: Go Laker Go
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders, fell back turn, 4wupper, empty

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 7 7F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 7000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF A RACE IN 2023 OR NON WINNERS OF FOUR RACES LIFETIME. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250. Colorado Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BULLAWAY was forwardly place down the backstretch, made a four wide bid on the turn to run down the leader in deep stretch and drove past. NO LIMITATION was within striking distance down the backstretch, then took the lead at the quarter pole but was caught in deep stretch but was able to hold off the late closing rival for the place. WILLTOBELUCKY was allowed to settle around the turn then moved out to three wide in upper stretch for a late rally but was too late. HAWKWOOD had to check early to avoid the loose rival but kept on to press the pace to the top of the stretch and weakened. GREY ROGUE went to the front to set a pressured pace to the top of the stretch and tired. FLY BUDDY FLY was never a threat. DIVINE TASK reared as the gates opened, lost rider and walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: No Limitation
ENTRY.COMMENT: within striking distance, led 1/4p, caught, held 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Bullaway
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly placed, 4wturn, ran down leader, drove past

ENTRY.NAME: Divine Task
ENTRY.COMMENT: reared start, lost rider, walked off

ENTRY.NAME: Willtobelucky
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, 3wupper, late rally, too late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 73. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 6200. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $3500 OR LESS IN 2022-2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $5000 OR COLORADO BRED CLAIMING PRICE $6250. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Colora do Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHE'S MY RIDE shared the command from between horses for the first quarter then edged away to a clear lead, was challenged at the quarter pole but dug in and drew off in the stretch to prove best. ALL NATIVE had no early speed and trailed the field to the three furlong marker then made a three or four wide bid, tipping out to four wide in upper stretch and made a late rally. DIVA'S DIVA vied for the early lead from the inside to midway down the backstretch then fell back around the turn, made a rail bid in the stretch to pass tiring rivals and be up for the show. AMERICAN REALITY stalked the pace down the backstretch then made a three wide bid on the turn but faltered. D'WILD MUFFIN had good early speed and shared command from three wide for the first quarter, then pressed the pace to the three furlong marker, moved to engage the leader at the quarter pole but had no late kick and tired. AWESOME SUNSET failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Diva's Diva
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied for lead, fell back, rail bid stretch, up show

ENTRY.NAME: She's My Ride
ENTRY.COMMENT: shared command, edged away, challenged, dug in, drew off,

ENTRY.NAME: D'wild Muffin
ENTRY.COMMENT: early speed, pressed pace, engaged leader, tired
